Here are both approaches:

## 1. Register the route (AppShell.xaml.cs)

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage (on item tap)

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

## 3. Receive on the ViewModel with IQueryAttributable

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string parameter arrives as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B — full object arrives as-is (no serialization)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire BindingContext on ProductDetailsPage

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **String params** are best for simple IDs — they survive deep links and are URI-safe.
- **`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`** avoids serialization and is ideal when you already have the object in memory, but won't work with URI deep links.
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called *after* construction, so you can handle both approaches in one method.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
